Class AbstractIDLeaseMap.LeaseEntry<K extends Lease>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.lease.AbstractIDLeaseMap.LeaseEntry<K>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<AbstractIDLeaseMap.LeaseEntry<K>>, Map.Entry<K,Long>
    Enclosing class:
    AbstractIDLeaseMap<K extends Lease>

    private static class AbstractIDLeaseMap.LeaseEntry<K extends Lease>
extends Object
implements Map.Entry<K,Long>, Comparable<AbstractIDLeaseMap.LeaseEntry<K>>
    The logic behind this Entry is that the identity which maintains strong references to the key and value will not be added to the set or leaseMap if it's already present.
